ZH: 我们在海边听着浪声入睡。
EN: We fell asleep listening to the sound of waves at the beach.

ZH: 这条小船在浪涌中颠簸不已。
EN: The small boat was tossed around in the surging waves.

ZH: 海浪拍打着礁石，发出阵阵巨响。
EN: The waves crashed against the rocks, creating a deafening noise.

ZH: 每当我看到海浪，就会想起小时候在海边玩耍的快乐时光。
EN: Whenever I see the waves, I think of the joyous times I had playing by the sea as a child.

ZH: 海浪的力量是如此强大，让人感到敬畏。
EN: The power of the waves is so strong that it inspires awe.

ZH: 海浪涌动，掀起了漫天白沫。
EN: The waves surged, creating a froth that covered everything.

ZH: 在扬子江边，浩浩汤汤的大浪翻滚不息。
EN: Along the Yangtze River, the immense waves rolled endlessly.

ZH: 他在巨浪中苦苦挣扎，终于得救了。
EN: He struggled in the huge waves but was finally rescued.

ZH: 风平浪静的海面上反射出了夕阳的余晖。
EN: The calm sea reflected the afterglow of the setting sun.

ZH: 浪花飞溅，阳光洒在我们身上。
EN: The spray from the waves splashed onto us as the sun shone down.

ZH: 海浪悄无声息地逼近着。
EN: The waves crept closer without a sound.

ZH: 沿着海岸，海浪不断地拍打着礁石。
EN: Along the coast, the waves kept crashing against the rocks.

ZH: 矗立在浪涛中的灯塔显得那么微弱。
EN: The lighthouse stood tall amidst the rolling waves, looking fragile.

ZH: 海浪起伏不定，时而宁静，时而狂暴。
EN: The waves rose and fell unpredictably, sometimes calm and sometimes violent.

ZH: 随着海浪的涌动，我们的小船摇摇欲坠。
EN: With the ebb and flow of the waves, our small boat teetered precariously.

ZH: 海上的浪花在月光下闪闪发光。
EN: The waves on the sea shimmered in the moonlight.

ZH: 每一个浪花都留下了它的记忆。
EN: Each wave left behind its own memory.

ZH: 浪潮滚滚，唤醒了沉睡的记忆。
EN: The surging waves stirred up dormant memories.

ZH: 浪潮汹涌，带来无尽的冲击。
EN: The raging waves brought endless turmoil.

ZH: 浪花飞溅，唯有深蓝的海水永恒不变。
